dataCsv.Site_Description: An old motorized wooden work boat about 22 feet in length, it lays 600 feet off Clayton’s west end waterfront.  The hull is upright with a slight lean to the port. Heavily covered in zebra mussels, the boat appears to have been striped before sinking. Wooded panels that supported a windshield are still in place. There is no motor, wheel, lights or metal work on the wreck.   This wreck is located about 50 feet east from the underwater power cable that feeds Grindstone Island from the village of Clayton.
